<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  I want the spell short-cut icons only..I want to do away with the back ground, like the old UI...it's not doable in the new one.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
That's not true. Go to the spellbar file and set <br>
<br>
Style_Transparent true /Style_Transparent <br>
<br>
(with the HTML brackets around the Style_transparent tags, stupid EZboard won't let me display them)<br>
<br>
for the main window. I have almost all of my windows set to be transparent, with just a simple non-titled border around them to mark them off, and alpha at 100% all the time because the faded look bothers me.<br>
<br>
The pointer thing HAS been around since the start of EQ, you've just been lucky enough not to see it. I get it on my Voodoo3 but not my GeForce3 (although I did for a while; it disappeared a few patches ago). The latest drivers are most definitely not always the best. (I couldn't get anything but 21.85 to work with my GeForce2.) Try some older drivers and see if they work better for you. Just make sure you completely uninstall your existing drivers first. You can get Detonator Destroyer to do that.<br>
<br>
I didn't even know you could doubleclick the top left icon to close a window. I dunno, I guess the nice clear X in the upper right next to the other icons was intuitive enough for me. Learn something new every day.<br>
